  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "SNES .srm = raw SRAM chip dump, no header. File size = SRAM size from ROM header $FFD8 (2^N KB). Common: 2KB=Final Fantasy VI/Chrono Trigger, 8KB=A Link to the Past (Zelda), 32KB=special cases. Layout is 100% game-specific. Some games append RTC data (e.g., Harvest Moon: 0x14 bytes at end for RTC state). Emulators: snes9x, bsnes, RetroArch save .srm as binary dump. Editing: use hex editor with game-specific SRAM map.",
